    <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:8px;text-align:center;">
      Large circle = LLM mean &nbsp;·&nbsp; Smaller shapes = individual baselines &nbsp;·&nbsp; Green zone = below both thresholds
    </p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- Metric Correlation (BERT × ROUGE-L) -->
  {% if has_bert and has_rouge %}
  <div class="card-full" style="margin-top:16px;padding-top:20px;border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:var(--muted2); margin-bottom:16px; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:3px;height:14px;border-radius:2px;background:var(--accent2);"></span>BERT vs ROUGE-L Correlation</div>
    
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <span class="ctrl-label">Baseline:</span>
      <select id="corrBaseline" onchange="rebuildCorrelation()">
        <option value="all">All (average)</option>
        {% for bl in baselines %}<option value="{{ bl }}">{{ bl }}</option>{% endfor %}
      </select>
    </div>
    
    <div class="card-full" style="background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <div class="card-title">BERTScore vs ROUGE-L Scatter — Field × Model</div>
      <div class="chart-description">
        Each point represents a (field, model) pair. X-axis = BERTScore, Y-axis = ROUGE-L. 
        Dashed diagonal = perfect correlation (r=1.0).
        <strong>Insight:</strong> Points clustered on diagonal = metrics are redundant; scattered points = complementary information.
      </div>
      <div style="position:relative;height:350px;width:100%;">
        <canvas id="correlationChart"></canvas>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-full" style="background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0;">
