      <span id="ieWeightLabel" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--accent);">70%</span>
      <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);">Text Quality: <span id="nlgWeightLabel">30%</span></span>
    </div>
    
    <div class="card-full" style="background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div class="card-title">Model Ranking Sensitivity — IE vs Text Quality Weighting</div>
      <div class="chart-description">
        Interactive analysis: adjust the IE (structured extraction) vs Text Quality (semantic + linguistic) weight using the slider above.
        <strong>Default: 70% IE + 30% Text Quality.</strong> Shows how model rankings change with different priority weightings.
        If rankings remain stable across weights, model performance is robust; if volatile, reliant on specific metric choice.
      </div>
      <div style="position:relative;height:320px;width:100%;">
        <canvas id="sensitivityChart"></canvas>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-full" style="background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div class="card-title">Ranking Stability Index</div>
      <div class="chart-description">Each row shows model rank under current weight setting. Compare with default to see sensitivity.</div>
      <table class="rank-table" style="width:auto;margin:0 auto;">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Model</th>
            <th>Current Rank</th>
            <th>Current Score</th>
            <th>IE Component</th>
            <th>Text Quality Component</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody id="sensitivityRankTable"></tbody>
      </table>
